","pron":"mil-khaw-maw'","derivation":"from H3898 (לָחַם) (in the sense of fighting);","strongs_def":"a battle (i.e. the engagement); generally, war (i.e. warfare)","kjv_def":"battle, fight(-ing), war(-rior).","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"war(158x), battle(151x), fight(5x)"},"H4422":{"id":"H4422","lemma":"מָלַט","translit":"mâlaṭ","pron":"maw-lat'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"properly, to be smooth, i.e. (by implication) to escape (as if by slipperiness); causatively, to release or rescue; specifically, to bring forth young, emit sparks","kjv_def":"deliver (self), escape, lay, leap out, let alone, let go, preserve, save, [idiom] speedily, [idiom] surely.","pos":"verb","usage":"escape(47x), deliver(33x), save(5x), alone(1x), lay(1x), preserve(1x), speedily(1x), surely(1x)"},"H4423":{"id":"H4423","lemma":"מֶלֶט","translit":"meleṭ","pron":"meh'-let","derivation":"from H4422 (מָלַט),","strongs_def":"cement (from its plastic smoothness)","kjv_def":"clay.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"clay(1x)"},"H4424":{"id":"H4424","lemma":"מְלַטְיָה","translit":"Mᵉlaṭyâh","pron":"mel-at-yaw'","derivation":"from H4423 (מֶלֶט) and H3050 (יָהּ); (whom) Jah has delivered;","strongs_def":"Melatjah, a Gibeonite","kjv_def":"Melatiah.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Melatiah(1x)"},"H4425":{"id":"H4425","lemma":"מְלִילָה","translit":"mᵉlîylâh","pron":"mel-ee-law'","derivation":"from H4449 (מְלַל) (in the sense of cropping (compare H4135 (מוּל)));","strongs_def":"a head of grain (as cut off)","kjv_def":"ear.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"ears(1x)"},"H4426":{"id":"H4426","lemma":"מְלִיצָה","translit":"mᵉlîytsâh","pron":"mel-ee-tsaw'","derivation":"from H3887 (לוּץ);","strongs_def":"an aphorism; also a satire","kjv_def":"interpretation, taunting.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"interpretation(1x), taunting(1x)"},"H4427":{"id":"H4427","lemma":"מָלַךְ","translit":"mâlak","pron":"maw-lak'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to reign; inceptively, to ascend the throne; causatively, to induct into royalty; hence (by implication) to take counsel","kjv_def":"consult, [idiom] indeed, be (make, set a, set up) king, be (make) queen, (begin to, make to) reign(-ing), rule, [idiom] surely.","pos":"verb","usage":"reign(289x), king(46x), made(4x), queen(2x), consulted(1x), indeed(1x), make(1x), rule(1x), set(1x), surely(1x)"},"H4428":{"id":"H4428","lemma":"מֶלֶךְ","translit":"melek","pron":"meh'-lek","derivation":"from H4427 (מָלַךְ);","strongs_def":"a king","kjv_def":"king, royal.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"royal(2x), Hammelech(1x), Malcham(1x), Moloch(1x)"},"H4429":{"id":"H4429","lemma":"מֶלֶךְ","translit":"Melek","pron":"meh'-lek","derivation":"the same as H4428 (מֶלֶךְ); king;","strongs_def":"Melek, the name of two Israelites","kjv_def":"Melech, Hammelech (by including the article).","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Melech(2x), Hammelech(1x)"},"H4430":{"id":"H4430","lemma":"מֶלֶךְ","translit":"melek","pron":"meh'-lek","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H4428 (מֶלֶךְ);","strongs_def":"a king","kjv_def":"king, royal.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"king(179x), royal(1x)"},"H4431":{"id":"H4431","lemma":"מְלַךְ","translit":"mᵉlak","pron":"mel-ak'","derivation":"(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H4427 (מָלַךְ) in the sense of consultation;","strongs_def":"advice","kjv_def":"counsel.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"counsel(1x)"},"H4432":{"id":"H4432","lemma":"מֹלֶךְ","translit":"Môlek","pron":"mo'-lek","derivation":"from H4427 (מָלַךְ);","strongs_def":"Molek (i.e. king), the chief deity of the Ammonites","kjv_def":"Molech. Compare H4445 (מַלְכָּם).","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Molech(8x)"},"H4433":{"id":"H4433","lemma":"מַלְכָּא","translit":"malkâʼ","pron":"mal-kaw'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H4436 (מַלְכָּה);","strongs_def":"a queen","kjv_def":"queen.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"queen(2x)"},"H4434":{"id":"H4434","lemma":"מַלְכֹּדֶת","translit":"malkôdeth","pron":"mal-ko'-deth","derivation":"from H3920 (לָכַד);","strongs_def":"a snare","kjv_def":"trap.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"trap(1x)"},"H4435":{"id":"H4435","lemma":"מִלְכָּה","translit":"Milkâh","pron":"mil-kaw'","derivation":"a form of H4436 (מַלְכָּה); queen;","strongs_def":"Milcah, the name of a Hebrewess and of an Israelite","kjv_def":"Milcah.","pos":"proper feminine noun","usage":"Milcah(11x)"},"H4436":{"id":"H4436","lemma":"מַלְכָּה","translit":"malkâh","pron":"mal-kaw'","derivation":"feminine of H4428 (מֶלֶךְ);","strongs_def":"a queen","kjv_def":"queen.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"queen(35x)"},"H4437":{"id":"H4437","lemma":"מַלְכוּ","translit":"malkûw","pron":"mal-koo'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H4438 (מַלְכוּת);","strongs_def":"dominion (abstractly or concretely)","kjv_def":"kingdom, kingly, realm, reign.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"kingdom(49x), reign(4x), realm(3x), kingly(1x)"},"H4438":{"id":"H4438","lemma":"מַלְכוּת","translit":"malkûwth","pron":"mal-kooth'","derivation":"or מַלְכֻת; or (in plural) מַלְכֻיָּה; from H4427 (מָלַךְ);","strongs_def":"a rule; concretely, a dominion","kjv_def":"empire, kingdom, realm, reign, royal.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"kingdom(51x), reign(21x), royal(13x), realm(4x), empire(1x), estate(1x)"},"H4439":{"id":"H4439","lemma":"מַלְכִּיאֵל","translit":"Malkîyʼêl","pron":"mal-kee-ale'","derivation":"from H4428 (מֶלֶךְ) and H410 (אֵל); king of (i.e. appointed by) God;","strongs_def":"Malkiel, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Malchiel.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Malchiel(3x)"},"H4440":{"id":"H4440","lemma":"מַלְכִּיאֵלִי","translit":"Malkîyʼêlîy","pron":"mal-kee-ay-lee'","derivation":"patronymical from H4439 (מַלְכִּיאֵל);","strongs_def":"a Malkielite or descendant of Malkiel","kjv_def":"Malchielite."},"H4441":{"id":"H4441","lemma":"מַלְכִּיָּה","translit":"Malkîyâh","pron":"mal-kee-yaw'","derivation":"or מַלְכִּיָּהוּlemma מַלְכִּיָהוּ missing dagesh, corrected to מַלְכִּיָּהוּ; (Jeremiah [38:6), from H442